HEADWORD: Gast
<hw>Gast</hw> <pr>(g⟦adot⟧st)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>gasten</ets>, <ets>g⟦aemac⟧sten</ets> to frighten, akin to Goth.
<ets>usgaisjan</ets>. See <er>Aghast</er>, <er>Ghastly</er>, and cf.
<er>Gaze</er>.]</ety> <def>To make aghast; to frighten; to terrify. See
<er>Aghast</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.
Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

